  "text": "(A) In Section 3, we provide an explicit construction of (n, d)-RPSs with redundancy at most 3d log n + 6.5 log n + O(1), along with an efficient locating algorithm of complexity O(n 3 ), for fixed d. This improves on Berkowitz and Kopparty's [CITATION_1] construction that requires 9d log n redundancy. Note that the sphere-packing bound suggests that the redundancy is log A − O(1). In Section 5, this construction is modified to produce positioning arrays which are robust to any errors of rank no more than a constant number. (C) In Section 6, we modify the construction of Berkowitz and Kopparty for (n, δn) q -RPSs by doubling the size of the alphabet. The relative distance δ is improved from max 1−R 3 , 1 − 3R to max 1−R 2 , 1 − 2R , where R is the rate. In contrast, the upper bound on the relative distance is 1 − R + o(1). (D) We determine the exact value of P (n, d) for d ≥ 2n/3 in Section 7 and construct a class of asymptotically optimal (n, n − 1) q -RPS for q = Ω(n 2+ ) in Section 8.",
